      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2011 BMW M3 (E92) powered by the iconic S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8, featuring individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio for a razor-sharp 8,400 RPM redline. This example features the 7-speed M-Double Clutch Transmission (M-DCT) with Drivelogic, delivering instantaneous shifts to the M-Variable differential lock. The suspension geometry remains precise, utilizing the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) system to manage rebound and compression across varying surfaces. Recent service includes a comprehensive analysis of the rod bearings and replacement of the throttle actuators, ensuring the VANOS system and valvetrain operate within factory tolerances. The hydraulic steering rack offers the tactile feedback modern EPS systems lack, making this a purist's choice for high-performance driving.",
